  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Slice your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin discs</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced potatoes</strong> to a heatproof bowl, then cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 8-10 min or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1--1709041310816-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1--1709041310816-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1--1709041310816-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1--1709041310816-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1--1709041310816-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are in the microwave, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once the steamed potatoes are done, remove the cling film to allow them to cool</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> lamb mince</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1709041315297-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1709041315297-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1709041315297-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1709041315297-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1709041315297-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once the meat has browned, reduce the heat to medium-high and add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>garlic </strong>with a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until the onion has slightly softened</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1709041319356-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1709041319356-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1709041319356-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1709041319356-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1709041319356-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[400ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>with your <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong> and <strong>mint sauce</strong> and mix it all together</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until the sauce has slightly thickened to a gravy-like consistency and the lamb is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>minty lamb mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1709041323913-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1709041323913-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1709041323913-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1709041323913-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1709041323913-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the sauce is thickening, add a layer of the <strong>steamed potatoes</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>(or two!)</p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, use individual dishes!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1709041328283-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1709041328283-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1709041328283-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1709041328283-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1709041328283-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top the layer of potatoes with the <strong>minty lamb mixture</strong> then finish with the <strong>remaining steamed potatoes</strong>, leaving gaps between the potato slices if possible</p><p>Top with a knob of<strong> butter</strong>, breaking it up over the potatoes, then season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Put the dish[es] in the oven for 15-20 min or until golden and bubbling – this is your <strong>Easter minty lamb & potato torte</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
